Sunderland are talking to free agent defender Anthony Reveillere.

The 34-year-old right-back was a target for QPR last year and was on a short term deal at Napoli last season.

The former France international is due to hold talks with manager Gus Poyet on Wednesday in the hope of proving he is fit enough to join their squad and play in the Premier League.

